# Codex Writer Findings — publicmenu
Chain: publicmenu-260408-071344-76bd

## Findings
1. [P1] Fix 1 config block is still on the old SOS request model — `HELP_REQUEST_TYPES` at `x.jsx:1796` still only allows `call_waiter`, `bill`, `napkins`, `menu`, `other`; `HELP_COOLDOWN_SECONDS` at `x.jsx:1799` still uses the old cooldown map; `HELP_CARD_LABELS` at `x.jsx:1800-1806` still exposes `help.bill` / `help.menu` and has no `plate`, `utensils`, `clear_table`, or `HELP_CARD_SHORT_LABELS`; `nonOtherTypes` at `x.jsx:2130` still omits the three new preset types. `HELP_PREVIEW_LIMIT` and `HELP_CHIPS` also remain defined at `x.jsx:1795` / `x.jsx:1807` and are still referenced at `x.jsx:2701`, `x.jsx:4935`, `x.jsx:5027`, and `x.jsx:5102`, so the Fix 1 cleanup has not landed in this revision. FIX: update the constants and `nonOtherTypes` to the v6.0 set, add `HELP_CARD_SHORT_LABELS`, and complete the deprecated `HELP_CHIPS` / `HELP_PREVIEW_LIMIT` cleanup in the matching revision.
2. [P1] Fix 2 urgency thresholds and helpers are missing entirely — there is no `HELP_URGENCY_THRESHOLDS`, `HELP_URGENCY_GROUP`, `getHelpUrgency`, or `getHelpTimerStr` anywhere in `x.jsx`; the help drawer still relies on the older wait/freshness helpers instead (`getHelpWaitLabel`, `getHelpReminderLabel`, `getHelpResolvedLabel`, `getHelpErrorCopy`, `getHelpFreshnessLabel` at `x.jsx:2554-2599`). FIX: add the two `useMemo` urgency maps immediately after `HELP_COOLDOWN_SECONDS` and add both `useCallback` helpers before render exactly as specified.
3. [P1] Fix 4 i18n additions are incomplete in both fallback dictionaries — the EN block still uses the old help drawer vocabulary (`help.bill`, `help.menu`, `help.comment_placeholder_other`, `help.submit_arrow`, `help.modal_desc`) and is missing the new v6.0 keys such as `help.get_bill`, `help.plate`, `help.utensils`, `help.clear_table`, all short-label keys, `help.subtitle_choose`, `help.table_default`, `help.cancel_confirm_q`, `help.cancel_keep`, `help.cancel_do`, `help.other_request_link`, `help.other_placeholder`, and `help.send_btn` (`x.jsx:525-553`). The RU block has `help.get_bill`, but it is still the old long copy `"Принести счёт"` and the block is missing the new additions including `help.plate`, `help.utensils`, `help.clear_table`, the short-label keys, `help.sent_suffix`, and `help.undo` (`x.jsx:590-607`). FIX: add the missing EN/RU fallback entries and replace RU `help.get_bill` with the shorter `"Счёт"` per spec, without duplicating keys that already exist correctly.

## Summary
Total: 3 findings (0 P0, 3 P1, 0 P2, 0 P3)

## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
- Overall clarity: 3
- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 1 — the prompt requires `HELP_CHIPS` and `HELP_PREVIEW_LIMIT` to be removed with zero occurrences while also forbidding JSX changes, but in the synced file those identifiers are still used by live render code at `x.jsx:2701`, `x.jsx:4935`, `x.jsx:5027`, and `x.jsx:5102`; it is unclear whether a paired JSX patch is assumed. Fix 1 — the prompt says `menu` must stay legacy-only and not be shown in the new preset set, but the current preset grid is hardcoded in JSX at `x.jsx:5048-5097`, so constant-only edits cannot make the visible card set match the six-button spec in this revision.
- Missing context (what info would have helped): The exact base commit / release expected for “SOS Help Drawer v6.0 Part A”, or confirmation that the companion JSX task for the frozen drawer UI is already merged.
- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): Whether this review should evaluate `origin/main` on 2026-04-08 only, or the combined Part A + paired frozen JSX state that the task text seems to assume.
